A man has died and three men have been hurt in a crash in Derby.Police were called to report of a crash involving a red Range Rover and a red Vauxhall Corsa in Pastures Hill, Littleover, shortly before 22:00 BST on Monday.Derbyshire Police said a 22-year-old man who was a passenger in the Corsa was treated by paramedics but died on the way to hospital.The driver of the Corsa, a 19-year-old man, remains in hospital with serious injuries, the force said, while another passenger in the Corsa, an 18-year-old man, and the driver of the Range Rover, a 57-year-old man, both received hospital treatment but have since been discharged.
Police said the family of the 22-year-old man have been informed of his death and are being supported by specialist officers.Officers would like to speak to anyone who witnessed the crash or who saw a red Corsa travelling in the area of Kenilworth Avenue shortly before the crash as well as anyone with dashcam footage to contact the force.Follow BBC Derby on Facebook, on X, or on Instagram. Send your story ideas to eastmidsnews@bbc.co.uk or via WhatsApp on 0808 100 2210.
